setwd ("/Users/nr267/Desktop/OVC_data/")
gsm.files <- list.files(".", pattern = "^GSM")

Helper function that reads a GSM file and returns a SingleCellExperiment.

readGSM <- function(gsm.files)
{
    gsm <- read.csv(gsm.files, as.is = TRUE, row.names = 1L)
    gsm <- t(gsm)
    SingleCellExperiment(assays = list(counts = gsm))    
}

sce1 <- readGSM(gsm.files[5])
sce2 <- readGSM(gsm.files[6])

gsm_combined <- cbind(sce1, sce2)

Trajectory inference

geneFilter <- apply(assays(gsm_combined)$counts,1,function(x) sum(x >= 3) >= 10)
gsm_combined_genefilter<- gsm_combined[geneFilter,]
FQnorm <- function(counts){
  rk <- apply(counts,2,rank,ties.method='min')
  counts.sort <- apply(counts,2,sort)
  refdist <- apply(counts.sort,1,median)
  norm <- apply(rk,2,function(r){ refdist[r] })
  rownames(norm) <- rownames(counts)
  return(norm)
}

assays(gsm_combined_genefilter)$norm <- FQnorm(assays(gsm_combined_genefilter)$counts)
pca <- prcomp(t(log1p(assays(gsm_combined_genefilter)$norm)), scale. = FALSE)
rd1 <- pca$x[,1:2]
plot(rd1, col = rgb(0,0,0,.5), pch=16, asp = 1)

diffusion_map <- DiffusionMap(t(log1p(assays(gsm_combined_genefilter)$norm)))
## Warning in DiffusionMap(t(log1p(assays(gsm_combined_genefilter)$norm))): You have 3941 genes. Consider passing e.g.
## n_pcs = 50 to speed up computation.
rd2 <- cbind(DC1 = diffusion_map$DC1, DC2 = diffusion_map$DC2)
plot(rd2, col = rgb(0,0,0,.5), pch = 16,asp = 1)

reducedDims(gsm_combined_genefilter) <- SimpleList(PCA = rd1, Diffap = rd2)

require(gam)

install.packages(gam)
## Error in install.packages : 'match' requires vector arguments
library(gam)

N <- gsm_combined_genefilter_ss$slingPseudotime_1

# for time, only look at the 100 most variable genes
Y <- log1p(assays(gsm_combined_genefilter_ss)$norm)
var100 <- names(sort(apply(Y,1,var),decreasing = TRUE))[1:100]
Y <- Y[var100,]

# fit a GAM with a loess term for pseudotime
gam.pval <- apply(Y,1,function(z){
  d <- data.frame(z=z, N=N)
  suppressWarnings({
    tmp <- suppressWarnings(gam(z ~ lo(N), data=d))
  })
  p <- summary(tmp)[3][[1]][2,3]
  p
})

topgenes <- names(sort(gam.pval, decreasing = FALSE))[1:100]
heatdata <- assays(gsm_combined_genefilter_ss)$norm[topgenes, order(N, na.last = NA)]
heatclus <- gsm_combined_genefilter_ss$GMM[order(N, na.last = NA)]

heatmap(log1p(heatdata), Colv = NA,
        ColSideColors = brewer.pal(9,"Set1")[heatclus])
